ARIMA RF

#Creating an Arima model
n=length(valid.xts)
train_date <- as.Date("2021/30/12",format="%Y/%d/%m")
tail(train.xts)
##             [,1]
## 2021-12-22 20.14
## 2021-12-23 20.25
## 2021-12-27 20.80
## 2021-12-28 20.76
## 2021-12-29 20.56
## 2021-12-30 20.47
fc.df <- vector()
i=1

while(i<=n){
  s=ymd(train_date)-14
  e=train_date
  test.xts <- window(F.xts, start = s, end = e)
  fit <- auto.arima(test.xts)
  predict <- forecast(fit, h=1)
  fc.df[i] <- predict$mean[1]
  train_date = ymd(train_date)+1
  i = i+1
}

valid.df$ARIMA.RF <- fc.df

Deep Learning Model

#Function to split the data

get_xy<-function(tsdata,NP)
{
  N <- length(tsdata)
  x<-matrix(nrow=N-NP,ncol=NP)
  y<-rep(0,N-NP)
  for (i in 1:(N-NP))
  {
    x[i,1:NP]<-as.numeric(tsdata[i:(i+NP-1)])
    y[i]<-as.numeric(tsdata[i+NP])
  }
  return(list(x,y))
}
model <- keras_model_sequential() %>%
layer_dense(units = 16, activation = "relu", input_shape = c(11)) %>%
layer_dense(units = 32, activation = "relu") %>% 
layer_dense(units = 64, activation = "relu") %>% 
layer_dense(units = 32, activation = "relu") %>% 
layer_dense(units = 16, activation = "relu") %>% 
layer_dense(units = 1)
## Loaded Tensorflow version 2.8.0
model %>% compile(
optimizer = "rmsprop",
loss = "mse",
metrics = c("mae"))
#Train x and y
a<-get_xy(train.ts,11)
train.x<-a[[1]]
train.y<-a[[2]]

#Test X and Y
a<-get_xy(as.ts(valid.xts),11)
test.x<-a[[1]]
test.y<-a[[2]]
early_stop<-callback_early_stopping(monitor="loss",patience=200)

model %>% fit( x = train.x, y = train.y, epochs = 200, 
validation_split = 0.3, verbose = 2 )
pred=model%>%predict(train.x)

forecast_dl <- model %>% predict(test.x)

plot(forecast_dl, type="l", ylab=" Closing Price", main="Deep Learning Model")
lines(test.y, lty=2, col="blue")

result<-model%>%evaluate(test.x,test.y)

result
##      loss       mae 
## 1.3330131 0.9065402
